{"title_page": "Taavi Vartia", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{more footnotes|date=November 2010}}\n'''Taavi Vartia''' (born 9 November 1965, in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]] is a Finnish [[Film director]], [[screenwriter|script writer]] and writer. Taavi Vartia has since 1990 planned, directed and produced programmes for all of Finland's national [[television channels]]: [[YLE TV1]], [[YLE TV2]], [[MTV3]] and [[Nelonen]], across a range of genres including [[Dramatic programming|drama]], entertainment, music, profiles and documentaries. He has been involved in the production of over 1100 episodes. Vartia has also written and directed several company- and image videos for the Finnish companies. In recent years he has received recognition as a writer of young adult dramas and as a documentary film maker. Vartia has published four novels.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://kirja.elisa.fi/?gclid=EAIaIQobChMIj_GwkLng6AIVGIuyCh04vgojEAAYASAAEgLphvD_BwE | title = Novels by Taavi Vartia| work = Elisa kirjat, Elisa Books| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref> Taavi Vartia founded Taaborin kes\u00e4teatteri/ Taabori Summer Theater in Nurmij\u00e4rvi<ref>{{cite web | url =https://www.taaborinkesateatteri.fi/ | title = Taabori Summer Theatre| work = Homepages.com| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref> 2009 and started to run the movie theatre Kino Juha<ref>{{cite web | url =https://www.kinojuha.fi/hosting/kinojuha.fi/| title = Cinema Kino Juha| work = Homepages| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref> 2019. Vartia is currently known to be the only Finnish film director to have his own cinema.\n\n==Feature Films==\n* ''[[R\u00f6lli ja kaikkien aikojen salaisuus/ Rolli and the Secret of All Times]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.matilarohr.com/index.php/en/productions/54-rolli-ja-kaikkien-aikojen-salaisuus |title = Rolli| work = MRP| accessdate = 16 September 2016}}</ref> Script writer and Director. Premier in September 2016.\n* ''[[Lomasankarit/ The Island of Secrets]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url =https://fi.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lomasankarit#cite_note-elokuvauutiset-4 |title = The Island of Secrets| work = Yellow Film & TV| accessdate = 31 October 2014}}</ref> Script writer and Director. Premier in October 2014.\n*''R\u00f6lli ja kultainen avain/ R\u00f6lli and the Golden Key]''.<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.matilarohr.com/index.php/en/productions/31-rolli-ja-kultainen-avain |title = Rolli and the Golden Key| work = MRP| accessdate = 20 February 2013}}</ref> Script writer and Director. Premiere in February 2013\n\n==Programmes==\n\n===Drama===\n*''Kevytt\u00e4 yl\u00e4pilve\u00e4/ World's safest place''<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.nurmijarvenuutiset.fi/artikkeli/852120-nurmijarvella-kuvattu-kevytta-ylapilvea-alkaa-torstaina-olen-todella-ylpea-tasta| title = Kevytt\u00e4 yl\u00e4pilve\u00e4| work = Nurmij\u00e4rvenuutiset.fi| accessdate = 25 March 2020}}</ref> (Elisa Viihde & Nelonen, Warner Bros./2020) 8 episodes. Original idea and director.\n*''Huone 301/ Man in Room 301''<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.wbitvpfinland.com/programme/102/huone-301| title = Man in Room 301| work = Warner Bros.fi| accessdate = 19 December 2019}}</ref> (Elisa Viihde & Warner Bros./2019) Co-Producer in Greece with Ikas Film & TV Productions.\n*''[[Keisari Aarnio/ King Liar]]''<ref>{{cite web | url =https://yellowfilm.fi/productions/king-liar/ | title = King Liar| work = Yellow Film & TV| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref> (Nelonen/ 2018), 10 episodes, directed 3.\n*''[[Syke/ Nurses]]'' <ref>{{cite web | url =https://yellowfilm.fi/productions/nurses/ |title = Nurses | work = Yellow Film & TV| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref> (TV1 & Nelonen/ 2015-2018). Director seasons 3. 5 abd 6. The third season won 2016 Kultainen Venla in category the best tv-programme.\n*''[[Downshiftaajat/ Downshifters]]''<ref>{{cite web | url =https://yellowfilm.fi/productions/downshifters/ | title = Downshifters| work = Yellow Film & TV| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref> (Elisa Viihde & YLE TV2/ 2016-2017). Director, season 2. \n*''[[:fi:K\u00e4enpes\u00e4|K\u00e4enpes\u00e4]]'' family drama (MTV3/ 2005\u20132006) 16 episodes. Director, one of many directors\n*''Suolaista vett\u00e4'' drama for young people (TV1/ 2000) 6 episodes. Script Writer (original theme by Kari Levola)\n*''[http://yle.fi/vintti/yle.fi/pertsajakilu/index.html Pertsan ja Kilun uudet seikkailut]'' drama for young people (TV2/ 2000). Director and Script writer. Actors: [[Santeri Kinnunen]], [[Vesa Vierikko]], [[Eija Vilpas]], [[Jaana Saarinen]], [[Ismo Apell]] and [[Tapio Liinoja]]\n*''[[:fi:Samaa sukua, eri maata|Samaa Sukua, eri maata]]'' family drama (TV1/ 1997\u201398) 46 episodes. Director\n*''Houdinin pojat'' mini serial (MTV3/ 1997) 4 episodes. Director, producer\n*''Is\u00e4ni on Supermies'' drama for young people (FST/ not filmed) 6 episodes. Script Writer (Script support by [[:sv:Nordiska Kulturfonden|Nordiska Kulturfonden]] 2001)\n*''Komisario Koivu'' detective comedy (TV1/ 1996) 28 episodes. Direction, one of many script writers\n*''Marskin poika'' television film (TV1/ 1995). Direction, dramatization\n*''Tapulikyl\u00e4'' family drama (TV1/ 1995) 5 episodes. Director\n\n===Entertainment & Talk Shows===\n*''Kuvia ja k\u00e4\u00e4nnekohtia/ Pictures and Turning Points''<ref>{{cite web | url = https://seura.fi/tv/poiminnat/kuvia-ja-kaannekohtia-sarjan-juontaja-taavi-vartian-mukaan-aitous-on-hanen-johtoajatuksensa-tv-isannan-tyossa/| title = Kuvia ja k\u00e4\u00e4nnekohtia| work = Seura.fi| accessdate = 5 March 2019}}</ref>(AlfaTV/2017-) . Producer, host.\n*''Kamera k\u00e4y/ Action'' (AlfaTV/2017-2018), 29 episodes. Producer and host with [[Jenni Banerjee]].\n*''[[:fi:Ota tai j\u00e4t\u00e4 (visailuohjelma)|Ota tai J\u00e4t\u00e4]]'' (Deal Or No Deal) format (Nelonen/ 2007) 10 episodes. Director\n*''[[:fi:Big Brother Suomi|Big Brother]]'' format (SubTv/ 2006) 6 episodes. Live-action director of first six parts\n*''P\u00e4\u00e4roolissa'' \"Lets make a film\"- entertainment (TV1/ 2005) 8 episodes. Director, Host\n*''[[Diili]]'' (The Apprentice) format (MTV3/ 2004) 15 episodes. Director\n*''Videotreffit'' video date entertainment for young people (TV2/ 1999) 18 episodes. Director\n*''[[Ben Furman]]'', talk show (TV1/1999) 18 episodes. Director\n*''Haastattelijana [[Mirja Pyykk\u00f6]]'', talk show (TV1/1995-97) 40 episodes. Director, Producer\n*''Sinun Unelmiesi T\u00e4hden'' human fantasies (TV1/ 1995) 10 episodes. Director\n*''Etusivu uusiksi'' press competition (TV2/ 1995) 50 episodes. Host\n*''T\u00e4m\u00e4 on minun'' quiz (TV1/ 1994) 18 episodes. Director\n*''Erotico-tico'' erotic sketch show (TV1/ 1992) 18 episodes. Director, Script Writer\n\n===Music Entertainment & Concerts===\n*''[[Sein\u00e4joen Tangomarkkinat/ Tango Festival in Sein\u00e4joki]] -concerts'' <ref>{{cite web | url = https://elonet.finna.fi/Search/Results?filter%5B%5D=author2_id_str_mv%3A%22kavi.elonet_yhtio_1490991%22&dfApplied=1&lookfor=taavi+vartia&type=AllFields&limit=50| title = Tangomarkkinat| work = Elonet.fi| accessdate = 12 July 2018}}</ref>(Alfa TV/2018): Queen's Final, King's Final, Meid\u00e4n Tango/ Our Tango -Concert and Semi Finals in Kerava. Director. \n*''[[Sein\u00e4joen Tangomarkkinat/ Tango Festival in Sein\u00e4joki]] -concerts'' (Alfa TV/2017): Queen's Final, King's Final, Tango Finlandia -Concert and Semi Finals in Kerava. Director. \n*''Kirka \u2013taiteilijajuhlakonsertti'' concert (TV1/ 1998). Director\n*''Toivomusl\u00e4hde'' (TV2/ 1998) 19 parts. Director\n*''Puhdas El\u00e4m\u00e4 Lapselle'' concerts 1996 and 1997 at the Olympic Stadium (MTV3). Director\n*''Euroviisut 1996'' Eurovision Song Contest, Finnish Competition (TV1/ 1999). Director\n*''Danny \u2013taiteilijajuhlakonsertti'' (TV1/ 1996). Director\n*''Sarajevo-konsertti'' at the Olympic Stadium (TV1/ 1995). Director, reporter\n*''Euroviisut 1994'' Eurovision Song Contest, Finnish Competition (TV1/ 1994). Director\n*''Katri Helena 50-v \u2013k