ion\n*''Orvot'' direct theatre play broadcasting from Kansallisteatteri/National Theatre (TV1/1997). TV Direction\n\n==Theatre==\nTaavi Vartia has directed numerous plays for the whole family at the Taaborin kes\u00e4tetatteri/ Taabor Summer Theater, which he founded in 2009.\nThe summer theater is based in Taaborinvuori/Nurmij\u00e4rvi, Finland.\n*2020 ''Vaahteram\u00e4en Eemeli/ That Boy Emil''. Playwright [[Astrid Lindgren]]. \n*2019 ''Tuhkimo/ Cinderella''. Playwright\n*2018 ''Peppi Pitk\u00e4tossu/ Pippi Longstocking''. Playwright [[Astrid Lindgren]]. \n*2017 ''Hein\u00e4hattu, Vilttitossu ja Rubensin veljekset''. Playwright [[Tiina Nopola]] and [[Sinikka Nopola]].\n*2016 ''Risto R\u00e4pp\u00e4\u00e4j\u00e4 ja Nelli Nuudelip\u00e4\u00e4''. Playwright [[Tiina Nopola]] and [[Sinikka Nopola]]\n*2015 ''Zorro''. Playwright Esa Silander. \n*2014 ''Peter Pan''. Playwright. \n*2013 ''Vaahteram\u00e4en Eemeli/ That Boy Emil''. Playwright [[Astrid Lindgren]]. \n*2012 ''Gangsteri ja kaunotar''. Playwright. \n*2011 ''Kaikkien aikojen Robin Hood/ The all-time Robin Hood''. Playwright\n*2009 ja 2010 ''Kaikkien aikojen Pertsa ja Kilu''. Playwright\n*2008 ''Kaikkien aikojen Pertsa ja Kilu''.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kirjurin.fi/historia_2008b.php| title = Pertsa ja Kilu| work = Kirjurin.fi| accessdate = 15 June 2008}}</ref> Kirjurinluodon kes\u00e4teatteri. Director and Playwright.\n\n==Novels==\n*''[http://paasilinna.pikakirjakauppa.fi/tuote/taavi_vartia/varastettu_vaimo/9789522990839 Varastettu Vaimo]'' (\"Stolen Wife\"),{{ISBN|9789522990839}}, {{ISBN|9522990833}}, published August 2015 by [http://paasilinna.fi/ Paasilinna Kustannus].\n*''[http://www.helsinkikirjat.fi/kirjat/tuulen-viema-mies Tuulen viem\u00e4 mies]'' (\"Man Gone with the Wind\"),pages 503, {{ISBN|978-952-5989-09-0}}, published August 2012 by [[Helsinki Kirjat]].\n*''[http://www.helsinkikirjat.fi/kirjat/viikinkipoika-kaspar-sininen-viikinki-ja-kuninkaan-sotaratsu Viikinkipoika Kaspar: Sininen Viikinki ja Kuninkaan sotaratsu]'' (\"The Viking Boy Kaspar: Blue Viking and war knight of the King\"),pages 392, {{ISBN|978-952-5874-57-0}}, published July 2011 by [[Helsinki Kirjat]].\n*''[http://www.helsinkikirjat.fi/kirjat/viikinkipoika-kaspar Viikinkipoika Kaspar]'' (\"The Viking Boy Kaspar\"), pages 239, {{ISBN|978-952-5874-22-8}}/ 978-952-5874-76-1 (ePub eBook). Published 2.February 2011 by [[Helsinki Kirjat]].\n*''[http://www.kauppakv.fi/sis/Otava/tuote/9789511270430 R\u00f6lli ja kultainen avain]'' (R\u00f6lli and the Golden Key), {{ISBN|9789511270430}}. Published January 2013 by [[:fi:Otava (kirjankustantamo)|Otava]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://taavivartia.fi// Official Homepages]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0890254/?ref_=fn_al_nm_1// IMDB]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vartia, Taavi}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Finnish television directors]]\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{no footnotes|date=November 2010}}\n'''Taavi Vartia''' (born 9 November 1965, in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]] is a Finnish [[Film director]], [[screenwriter|script writer]] and writer. Taavi Vartia has since 1990 planned, directed and produced programmes for all of Finland's national [[television channels]]: [[YLE TV1]], [[YLE TV2]], [[MTV3]] and [[Nelonen]], across a range of genres including [[Dramatic programming|drama]], entertainment, music, profiles and documentaries. He has been involved in the production of over 1100 episodes. Vartia has also written and directed several company- and image videos for the Finnish companies. In recent years he has received recognition as a writer of young adult dramas and as a documentary film maker. Vartia has published four novels<ref>{{cite web | url = https://kirja.elisa.fi/?gclid=EAIaIQobChMIj_GwkLng6AIVGIuyCh04vgojEAAYASAAEgLphvD_BwE | title = Novels by Taavi Vartia| work = Elisa kirjat, Elisa Books| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref>. Taavi Vartia founded Taaborin kes\u00e4teatteri/ Taabori Summer Theater in Nurmij\u00e4rvi<ref>{{cite web | url =https://www.taaborinkesateatteri.fi/ | title = Taabori Summer Theatre| work = Homepages.com| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref> 2009 and started to run the movie theatre Kino Juha<ref>{{cite web | url =https://www.kinojuha.fi/hosting/kinojuha.fi/| title = Cinema Kino Juha| work = Homepages| accessdate = 30 January 2020}}</ref> 2019. Vartia is currently known to be the only Finnish film director to have his own cinema.\n\n==Feature Films==\n* ''[[R\u00f6lli ja kaikkien aikojen salaisuus/ Rolli and the Secret of All Times]]''<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.matilarohr.com/index.php/en/productions/54-rolli-ja-kaikkien-aikojen-salaisuus |title = Rolli| work = MRP| accessdate = 16 September 2016}}</ref>. Script writer and Director. Premier in September 2016.\n* ''[[Lomasankarit/ The Island of Secrets]]''<ref>{{cite web | url =https://fi.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lomasankarit#cite_note-elokuvauutiset-4 |title = The Island of Secrets| work = Yellow Film & TV| accessdate = 31 October 2014}}</ref>. Script writer and Director. Premier in October 2014.\n*''R\u00f6lli ja kultainen avain/ R\u00f6lli and the Golden Key]''<ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.matilarohr.com/index.php/en/productions/31-rolli-ja-kultainen-avain |title = Rolli and the Golden Key| work = MRP| accessdate = 20 February 2013}}</ref> . Script writer and Director. Premiere in February 2013\n\n==Programmes==\n\n===Drama===\n*''Kevytt\u00e4 yl\u00e4pilve\u00e4/ World's safest place''<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.nurmijarvenuutiset.fi/artikkeli/852120-nurmijarvella-kuvattu-kevytta-ylapilvea-alkaa-torstaina-olen-todella-ylpea-tasta| title = Kevytt\u00e4 yl\u00e4pilve\u00e4| work = Nurmij\u00e4rvenuutiset.fi| accessdate = 25 March 2020}}</ref> (Elisa Viihde & Nelonen, Warner Bros./2020) 8 episodes. Original idea and director.\n*''Huone 301/ Man in Room 301''<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.wbitvpfinland.com/programme/